The Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse (OUTA) is this morning alongside the South African Council of Churches (SACC), briefing parliaments Portfolio Committee on Public Enterprises ahead of the inquiry into power utility Eskom.The briefings by the organisations are meant to provide information to the committee while it gears up for its full-scale inquiry.The groups have recently published various reports attempting to detail incidents of state capture at State owned enterprises. Parliament is listening to the people, said OUTA Chief Operating Officer, Ben Theron.Last month the committee adopted the terms of reference of the inquiry which is set to begin during the first week of August.The terms include the Eskom s boards response to the State of Capture report, how former CEO Brian Molefe s retirement package was determined as well as the decision to reappoint after he left the utility in November 2016.Coal contracts at the power utility are also set to be scrutinised as well as the manner in which it appoints and remunerates board members and executive management.-TNA Reporter